original_title: Five Bucks at the Door: The Story of Crocks N Rolls
overview: A documentary discussing the legacy and impact of the famous Crocks N Rolls bar, a music club in Thunder Bay, Ontario that featured many prominent artists throughout the 1980s. Numerous interviewees are profiled, as is the club's legendary founder and owner Frank Loffredo.
tagline: How A Bar in the Middle of Nowhere Put Canadian Music on the Map
title: Five Bucks at the Door: The Story of Crocks N Rolls
